snippet.textDisplay:
I'm French and confined in my home with the love of my life and our big dog in very lucky conditions (big house with a garden, etc).. Our 4 adult kids (youngest is 18) are safe and isolated apart from us (TG!! we love them but they are driving us crazy after a couple of hours !!! :D ) and at their "home" (one of our daughters is isolated in South NZ in her van where she lives happily !!).

I don't know much about American shows, including The Office because we never wanted tv at home to preserve our family life. So I only know you and Steve through your guys' movies and I love you guys so much. So a BIG THANK YOU for doing this because you're not only entertaining America but also the rest of the English-speaking world !! If you need a local correspondant in Paris' area (I'm not that rich to live inside Paris, don't push it !! :D) feel free to let me know !

THANK YOU again and hope the laughters and fun moments helps very much those who need them. Take you all great care of yourseves. Cécile.

snippet.textDisplay: My daughters age 9 and 12 are huge Office fans. We have to FF through so much of the inappropriate content on the show, because I didn’t realize how not kid friendly the show is, and 15 years ago I didn’t really stick with it when it was on network TV past season 3, but now we’ve watched every single episode. We love The Office. Now we are rewatching again because my kids love the show so much! I’ve seen Pretzel Day about 40 times because they just crack up so much at Stanley’s big eyes. The Fired drill is hands down the best episode of all Office episodes we think. The Hamilton Zoom SGN was by far the most awesome Zoom ever. My kids went nuts because they are Hamilton fanatics too! Great job John & Emily!

snippet.textDisplay:
Our school, Primrose School of West Chester closed due to Corona Virus. Our last 2 days of school we had our teachers record videos of them doing curriculum activities and just saying hi. We created a facebook page and invited all of our teachers and families to join. Every day we post pre recorded videos and greetings from our teachers. Some teachers have even continued to record themselves at home reading books and posted them. Our school chef shares healthy recipes. Our families and teachers continually post pictures. It is a fantastic way for us to stay connected and our students are loving seeing their teachers and friends! I am in awe at how connected we have been able to be and the love and support our teachers and families have shared.
#somegoodnews
